    <stitle>REPAIR INSTRUCTIONS FOR FIBERGLASS AND PLASTIC (ABS) MATERIAL - FIBERGLASS - PREPARATION PROCEDURE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1600301" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>PREPARATION PROCEDURE</title>
        <para>Prepare for all body repairs using fiberglass by following these steps:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check shop temperature and humidity and compare with specifications on the label for the
                material being used. A temperature of 70&#176;F (21&#176;C) and 70% humidity are considered ideal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Gather required materials.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean and inspect damaged area.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push on surrounding area and underneath damaged area to determine extent of damage.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
